2. Identification of Issues

The collected sentences contain the following problems:

Slang Words
OMG → Oh My God
lol → Laughing Out Loud
brb → Be Right Back
idk → I Don’t Know
rn → Right Now
asap → As Soon As Possible
Emojis
😂 🤣 😡 😴 🔥 ❤️ 😭 😍 👍 😅
These represent emotions but are not directly understandable by machines.
Typos (Spelling Errors)
gud → good
beleive → believe
Ths → This
prperly → properly
hve → have
undrstand → understand

3. Preprocessing Techniques Needed

To handle messy text, the following preprocessing steps are required:

1. Lowercasing

Convert all text into lowercase to maintain consistency.
Example: “OMG” → “omg”

2. Removing Punctuation and Special Characters

Remove symbols like “!!!”, “??”, etc., which do not add meaning.

3. Expanding Slang and Abbreviations

Convert slang into full forms.
Example: “idk” → “I do not know”

4. Removing or Converting Emojis

Either remove emojis or convert them into meaningful words.
Example: 😂 → “happy” or “laugh”

5. Spelling Correction

Fix typos using libraries or dictionaries.
Example: “gud” → “good”

6. Tokenization

Split sentences into individual words or tokens.

7. Stopword Removal

Remove common words like “is”, “the”, “and” that do not add much meaning.

8. Stemming / Lemmatization

Convert words to their base form.
Example: “running” → “run”

